result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th) and Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Carol L Jensen was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: FROM DEFENSE ATTY REQUESTING CLAIRIFICATION ON JOC

Defendant Carol L Jensen in court with attorney Dennis James Sieg.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states that Atty Sieg did call to get this rescheduled however, the defendant came and wanted to proceed today.  Atty Sieg agrees.
  Atty Hendee states plea agreement to Ct. 1.  Atty Sieg agrees.  Defendant agrees and enters a Guilty plea.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.  

BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Ct. 1.  

Atty Hendee moves to dismiss Ct. 2 and makes sentencing arguments.
Atty Sieg makes sentencing arguments.  Atty Sieg asks for the reduced IID as the defendant is not working.  Atty Sieg asks for huber for job searches.
Defendant makes a statement to the court.

BY THE COURT:  Ct. 1:  Withhold Sentence; 3 years Probation with conditions:
*6 months in the Marquette County Jail w/huber
*Report forthwith
*Good Time
*First 48 hours will be without huber
*Huber to include treatment
*Pay fine and costs = $2,198.00
*DNA Sample + $250.00 DNA Surcharge 
*36 months DL Revocation and Ignition Interlock.  Court will allow the reduced rate of the IID.
*AODA and any follow-up treatment
*Absolute Sobriety; zero tolerance
*Credit = 2 days if revoked
Bond to be applied
Ct. 2 to be dismissed.
  **Court advises defendant that they have been convicted of a Felony and advises rights of voting privileges and of owning a firearm.

Defendant Carol L Jensen in court with attorney Dennis James Sieg.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states that he was informed from Atty Sieg that the defendant would be waiving the Prelim.  
   Atty Sieg agrees and has discussed the waiver with his client.  Court questions the defendant.  Defendant agrees with the waiver.  Court accepts the waiver of the Prelim.

  BY THE COURT:  Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed and this defendant committed it.  Case bound over for trial or further proceedings.

Atty Hendee files the information with the Court.  Atty Hendee states that there is no BAC on the information due to the State does not have that information yet; once that happens, the State will fine an amended information.  Atty Sieg states that the Defendant received a copy of the information and waives its reading.  
  Defendant stands mute.  Attorney request the Court enter a Not Guilty plea on behalf of the defendant.

  BY THE COURT:  Court enters a Not Guilty plea on behalf of the defendant.
Set for Return.
bond continued.  Return date scheduled for November 19, 2015 at 02:30 pm.

Defendant Carol L Jensen in court, in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states charges and states probable cause.  
Court finds probable cause.
  Court advises defendant of right to an attorney.  Defendant states that she will get an Attorney.  Court confirms defendant's address.  Atty Hendee requests a $500 cash bond with conditions.
Defendant questions the fact that the DA is saying this is her 5th offense and she said that this should only be her 4th.  Defendant asks the DA to repeat the offense dates.
Atty Hendee repeats the offense and conviction dates to the court.
Court advises the defendant that she will have to talk with her Attorney regarding that.  Defendant agrees.

  BY THE COURT:  Court sets a $500 cash bond with conditions:
*Absolute Sobriety; zero tolerance
  Initial appearance scheduled for August 24, 2015 at 02:30 pm.
